parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes a loud noise
the vehicle jerks or bucks
the transmission fails to shift into gear
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key can be removed from the ignition while the vehicle is in gear
the ignition switch is worn down
the vehicle stalls or fails to start
the key is stuck in the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The slipping of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key sticks or gets stuck in the ignition
the key falls out of the ignition while the car is on
the car shuts off while driving
the steering wheel locks
the horn fails to work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the warning lights illuminate
the airbag warning light illuminates
the horn fails to work
the wipers fail to work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
often without warning
and may exhibit symptoms such as hesitation
sputtering
or a loud humming noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving.
symptoms: The timing chain breaks or fails
often causing the engine to make a loud slapping or whirring noise
and may result in engine damage or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or slip out of gear, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips
hesitates
or fails to engage properly
often causing the vehicle to jerk or lurch while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the engine
often causing the engine to overheat or seize
and may result in engine damage or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition and electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The ignition system fails
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power
and may exhibit symptoms such as a faulty ignition coil
spark plugs
or module.
